{"serial": "00071", "department_serial": 4, "code": "LN1006", "class": "E", "name": {"en": "Freshman English as an Introduction to Management", "ch": "大一英文:管理課群"}, "notice": {"en": "Course level: intermediate.", "ch": "中級課程。"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Wang, Li-Jen"], "ch": ["王立仁"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "O", "room": "313"}}, {"time": {"week": 5, "session": ["2"]}, "loc": {"building": "O", "room": "314"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": true, "MaxStu": 45, "department": {"ch": "語言中心", "en": "Language Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "部分英語", "en": "Partially English"}, "card": {"ch": "全部使用", "en": "All"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 42, "remark": {"ch": "中級課程。", "en": "Course level: intermediate."}, "goal": {"ch": "新制大一英文課程目標 CEFR B2 15 Descriptors\nListening 聽力\n1. 能聽懂用標準口語所說的內容大意。\n2. 能在主題熟悉的情況下，了解大部分音檔和影片的重點。\n3. 能在講者陳述清晰的情況下，了解個人專業領域內的課程或演講。\nSPEAKING - Spoken Production  口語發表\n4. 在事先準備的情況下，能就感興趣的主題進行發表，並詳盡描述內容。\n5. 能透過提出論點、利弊、或因果關係等方法，來表達對一個議題的看法。\nSPEAKING - Spoken Interaction  口語互動\n6. 能以一定的流暢度、自然地進行口語互動。\n7. 能在努力投入的情況下，跟上並參與小組討論。\nREADING 閱讀\n8. 能快速瀏覽長篇複雜文本並掌握所需的細節。\n9. 能搜尋和瀏覽多個資料出處以獲取相關資訊。\n10. 能理解個人專業領域或感興趣主題的文本大意。\n11. 閱讀文章時能了解作者的觀點。\nWRITING 寫作\n12. 能寫出拼字和標點符號用法正確的文章。\n13. 能寫出描述清楚、提供細節的文章。\n14. 能寫出結合多個來源想法的文章。\n15. 能寫出清楚的理由來支持自己的論點。", "en": "新制大一英文課程目標 CEFR B2 15 Descriptors\n\nListening\n1. I can understand the main ideas of what is said to me in standard spoken English. \n2. I can understand the main ideas of most audios and videos of familiar topics.\n3. I can follow a lecture or talk within my own field if the presentation is clear.\n\nSPEAKING - Spoken Production\n4. I can give a clear, prepared presentation about topics I am interested in and provide detailed descriptions.\n5. I can express my opinion on an issue by giving reasons, talking about the advantages and disadvantages, or analyzing cause and effect.\n\nSPEAKING - Spoken Interaction\n6. I can interact quite fluently and naturally in conversations.\n7. I can, with some effort, keep up with and contribute to group discussions.\n\nREADING\n8. I can scan quickly through long and complex texts and find the details I want.\n9. I can search and browse various sources to obtain relevant information.\n10. I can understand the main ideas of reading materials within my field of study or of my interest.\n11. I can understand the writer’s point of view when reading an article.\n\nWRITING\n12. I can write an essay with reasonably accurate spelling and punctuation.\n13. I can write an essay with clear descriptions and proper details.\n14. I can write an essay combining the ideas from multiple sources.\n15. I can write an essay giving reasons to support my point of view."}, "outline": {"ch": "中級班課程:\n週次\nW1 課程介紹/ U7 Warm up\nW2-W5 U7 Customs and behavior\n閱讀、聽力、口說、寫作\n講授、討論及學生演示及寫作\nW6 簡報技巧及準備週\nW7 簡報準備週\nW8 小組簡報1\nW9-W10 U11 Knowledge and learning\n閱讀、聽力、口說、寫作\n講授、討論及學生演示\nW11 寫作技巧講授及作業\nW12-W13 U12 Money\n閱讀、聽力、口說、寫作\n講授、討論及學生演示\nW14 寫作技巧講授及小組簡報準備\nW15 小組簡報2\nW16 期末評量\n第13至15週進行CEFR問卷\n(更多細節請見第一週課堂的每周授課進度表)", "en": "Intermediate level:\nW1 Course overview/ U7 Warm up\nW2-W5 U7 Customs and behavior\nReading、Listening、Speaking、Writing\nLecturing, Discussion, Student presentation, and Writing\nW6 Presentation skills and preparation\nW7 Presentation preparation\nW8 Group preparation 1\nW9-W10 U11 Knowledge and learning\nReading、Listening、Speaking、Writing\nLecturing, Discussion, Student presentation, and Writing\nW11 Writing skills and writing assignment\nW12-W13 U12 Money\nReading、Listening、Speaking、Writing\nLecturing, Discussion, Student presentation, and Writing\nW14 Writing skills and Presentation preparation\nW15 Group presentation 2\nW16 Final exam\nweek 13-week15 CEFR B2 Survey\n(For more details, please refer to the weekly plan, which will be given to students in week 1)"}, "textbook": {"ch": "中級班課程教材:\n課本:Life 5\n輔助教材:\nThe Economist, BBC Ideas, The Atlantic, Forbes, TED, etc.", "en": "Intermediate level:\nTextbook: Life 5\nSupplementary material:\nThe Economist, BBC Ideas, The Atlantic, Forbes, TED, etc."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "10", "en": "10"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n\n\n\n其他", "en": ["Lecture", "", "", "", "Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "中級班課程:\n出席率10％\n課程參與10％\n作業10％\n小考10％\n小組報告及互評35％\n期末評量 20％      \n英語自學活動 5％", "en": "Intermediate level:\nAttendance 10％\nParticipation 10$\nAssignment 10％\nQuiz 10％\nGroup presentation and peer review 35％\nFinal exam 20％\nSelf study activity 5％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期三 2,3,4節", "en": "Wednesday 9:00-11:50"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "學生須完成課程反思", "en": "Students are required to finish self-reflection"}, "domain": {"ch": "基礎英文", "en": "基礎英文"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "語言溝通", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現", "自我評量/同儕互評", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "文化視野", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現", "其他"]}, {"competencies": "自主學習", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現", "自我評量/同儕互評", "作品/創作展演"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Language & Communication Skills", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance", "Self Assessment/ Peer Assessment", "Products/Creative Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Intercultural Literacy", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance", "Others"]}, {"competencies": "Self-directed Lifelong Learning", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance", "Self Assessment/ Peer Assessment", "Products/Creative Performance"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["系所:限企業管理學系、經濟學系。年級:限一年級。身份:限非交換生。"], "en": ["Department:Department of Business Administration、Department of Econom